Business Brief -- Park-Ohio Industries Inc.:
   Holder Secom General Says
   It Plans Board Nominations
Park-Ohio, a Cleveland machinery and forged products
concern, also said it had received a letter from Warren
Lichtenstein, a partner in Steel Partners L.P., a private New
York investment firm, seeking Park-Ohio's shareholder list
and other information for the purpose of commuication with
shareholders of Park-Ohio. Steel Partners says it has a
holding of less than 5% in Park-Ohio.
   Secom's three nominees are Roy McKnight, David Marczak and
Gerald Theisen, all Secom directors and officers. Secom,
Novi, Mich., is involved in metal parts forming, toolmaking
and plastic molded products.